Description: Fragment of lip and neck with complete oval handle from a Thasian pottery transport amphora. Finger mark at base of handle. Clay near fine micaceous light brown; blue-grey core. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and phiale and corn ear symbols.
Dimensions: Diameter: 34.30 centimetres (maximum diameter, est., at lower shoulder break)
Curator's comments: Garlan, Y., Les timbres amphoriques de Thasos. 1, Timbres protothasiens et thasiens anciens (Paris 1999) 586. Name Euphra........
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0005)
